10:
This must be their primary
function—feeding off of hidden
emotions to keep themselves
operating.
13:
They read people's thoughts and
speak them out loud—
26:
G-get back, Mary! You'll get caught,
too!
31: Will, NO! I can't let them just—
34:
Yeah, I have to help you! If I left you
here, I'd be all by myself again!
36:
You always come see me when I'm
lonely, and you tell me everything I
want to hear. You're just so
convenient, Will!
38:
I don't need to tell you how I really
feel, since I might lose you anyway.
And who knows if I'd be able to find
someone else?
40:
I have to be kind, or you won't be
here to pay attention to me
anymore.
48:
I hated the days where I got nothing
but rejection from others.
49:
As long as I'm careful with what I say
and I hide how awful I really am,
she'll stay with me.
55:
I can't stand the thought of Mary
leaving me because I got brave and
said something stupid.
57:
I don't care if she uses me because
I'm convenient, or if she just spends
time with me out of pity. As long as
she keeps being nice to me, I don't
care.
59:
All I have to offer her are my selfish,
ugly feelings. So a bit of attention is
about as much as someone like me
can expect.
72:
But I won't just give up on you! Why
don't you understand how
important you are to me?!
76:
I won't give up on my feelings, and I
won't give up on yours, either!
79:
I knew all along, Will! I knew that
everyone else also realized how
lonely I really was...
83:
And I knew you admired me
because I was the first person to be
nice to you!
88: But I was still happy anyway!
93:
Your smile was enough for me to be
happy I was here!
96:
The person who gave me all this
happiness was YOU, Will!
100:
You're more special to me than
anyone! I need you to understand
that NOBODY can replace you!
107:
I... I didn't admire you because you
were nice to me!
110:
Your smile is what I admired... And I
wanted to do everything I could to
protect it!
113:
No matter how terrified I was of
rejection, I knew I had to try to be by
your side!
147: Good job, Mary! You finally did it!
156:
You did your best, and your best
was perfect!
164:
You've done it, Mary. As the Heir to
House Felder, I congratulate you on
this momentous achievement.
167:
...You really gave it your all. It's an
honor to call you my friend!
178:
You guys really don't know when to
shut up, do you?
182:
Everyone has their strengths and
flaws. We're all just trying to do our
best with what we've got!
186:
But you jerks just zero in on the ugly
parts! Stop messing with people
who are just doing their best to
move forward!
190:
People have long been aware of
each other's malignant tendencies,
and society itself is the arbiter.
192:
As an arbiter of House Felder I strive
to maintain equilibrium...
196:
BUT! If you think I'm gonna forgive
you for running your mouth, you
better get ready to be blasted full of
holes!
206:
They... merged? Can machines do
that?
210:
Well, Mary. It looks like we're not
done here yet!
214:
It's no match for us! Let's see this
thing through to the bitter end!
233: I'll help too! Let's go, everyone!
